*This promo has me all fuzzy of heartfelt warmth!!*

Ahh godness, it's both so cute and hilarious at the same time ^__^ I feel all "bubbly and sparkly" inside, after viewing it. *LOL.*... And that dachshund sequence - kill me, it's absolutely _HILARIOUS_. That's a core deep- on solid levelbased humour!

***I actually happen to have a gut sensation this animated movie can reach the status of classics of all time (if it'll succeed in perfection, so to speak) , and thereby never be forgotten!***... But we'll see about that!

Only hope it'll keep up the high level of amusement, and not turn monotonous and tedious _at length!_... - Would truely be a shame in that case. Well, obviously they're working their swet "strenuously", at puzzling its story-arc and concluding a finish, to make its outcome amplified enough, or more so. Maybe the production crew has just even begun its process in making. _Why the heck else premiere in 2016??....._ ^^'

(after watching the dachshund clip numerous times). What I also like about this whole clip is the interiors of the rooms. Sweet Pea's owner is very techie;he even has surround sound speakers. Gidget matches the all-white minimalist decor. In contrast, Max lives in a brownstone,and Katie herself has a bit of ecclectic taste in decor. The dachshund's kitchen is lovely and warm;the whole house is probably very homey, and the owner could be a foodie (with a mixer like that and a very thick cookbook on the counter). Chloe's owner is a bit retro, loves to cook for the sake of cooking. Probably has family dinners every Sunday
. And she loves maple syrup! Mel's apartment has loads of natural light with those windows. I see his owner appreciating things like books or painting,maybe And well, Leonard's surrounded by 18th-19th century stuff, plus one awesome stereo!
